<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">Dealing With Bad Tiles</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">2-letter words · Bingo</p>


      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>7 min read</span>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">Every Scrabble player knows the sinking feeling: you draw seven tiles and stare at UUOIIW. No consonants, no scoring power, no obvious words. Bad racks are inevitable — roughly one in four draws will feel unplayable. The difference between average and expert players is what happens next.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Three Types of Bad Racks</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🟡 Vowel Flood (5+ vowels)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Example: A E I O U A E — no consonant structure to build around. Limited to short words and vowel dumps.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔵 Consonant Cluster (5+ consonants)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Example: B C G K P T W — need to find existing vowels on the board to play through. Often requires an exchange.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🟣 Duplicate Overload (3+ of same letter)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Example: I I I N T S R — duplicates reduce anagram possibilities by 60-80%. Shed extras fast.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Vowel Dump Strategy</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300">When you're flooded with vowels, your goal is to play 2-3 vowels per turn without scoring zero. Memorise these high-vowel words:</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Score</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Vowels Dumped</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Notes</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">ADIEU</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Best vowel dump in the game</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">OURIE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Shivery; SOWPODS only</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">AUDIO</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Common word, easy to place</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">URAEI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Plural of uraeus (cobra)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">EAU</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">French for water; valid in SOWPODS</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">AGIO</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Currency exchange premium</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">A 6-point vowel dump that leaves you with <span class="text-white font-medium">RSTNE</span> is worth more than a 15-point play that leaves you with <span class="text-white font-medium">UUOII</span>. Always evaluate by rack leave quality, not just immediate score.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Consonant Cluster Survival</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300">All-consonant racks require the board to save you. Look for existing vowels you can play through:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play through existing vowels:</span> Look for exposed A, E, I, O on the board. Even a simple 3-letter word like CWM or TSK uses no vowels at all.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Know your no-vowel words:</span> CWM, CRWTH, GYM, GLYPH, LYMPH, MYTH, NYMPH, PSYCH, SHY, THY, WHY, PYGMY — all playable without vowels on your rack.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target hook letters:</span> An exposed -E or -A on the board lets you front-hook or back-hook using only consonants from your rack (SH + E = SHE).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Exchange if stuck:</span> If no play scores above 8-10 points with a consonant-heavy rack, exchange 4-5 consonants. Keep any S, blank, or power tile (Z, X, J).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
